Executing the code based on the conditions is called conditional statements.
IF:  Synatx
if (condition) {
Write statements here;
}
Ex:
var a = 20;
var b = 10;
if (a > b) {
}
alert("a is greater than b.");
}

 IF else: syntax
if(condition) {
if statements here;
else{
else statement here;
}
Ex:
var a = 10;
var b= 20;
if (a > b) {
}
alert("a is greater than b.");
}
else{
alert("b is greater than a.");
}



<html>
